<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11778] HiveContext.read.table does not support user-specified database names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11778</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we have defined a HiveContext instance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;val hiveContext = new org.apache.spark.sql.hive.HiveContext(sparkContext)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;then&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hiveContext.table(&quot;db_name.table&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;works but&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hiveContext.read.table(&quot;db_name.table&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;throws an &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.spark.sql.catalyst.analysis.NoSuchTableException&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
However,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hiveContext.sql(&quot;use db_name&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
hiveContext.read.table(&quot;table&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;works as expected&lt;/p&gt;</description>
